1. CHEESE WHIZZ 1) Preheat the oven to 180 C.2) In a bowl, whisk 3 extra-large eggs. Season with salt, pepper and a pinch of chilli flakes if desired. Stir in a large handful of grated mature cheddar cheese.3) Place 6 slices of white bread on a baking tray and divide the egg mixture between the slices. Bake for 10 minutes until puffed up and golden brown. Serve immediately with tomato sauce if desired. Serves 4-6 How to cook eggs perfectly, any way, every time 2. GLUTEN-FREE SPONGE CAKE 1) Preheat the oven to 180 C.2) In the bowl of an electric mixer, beat 250g caster sugar with 250g softened butter till creamy.3) With the machine running, add 4 extra-large eggs, beating between each addition.4) Add 5ml (1 tsp) vanilla extract and 220g (2 cups) self-raising, self-binding rice flour. Beat till just blended.5) Line the base of a 20cm loose-bottomed pan with greaseproof paper and spoon in the batter. Bake for 30-40 minutes.6) Cool in pan for 5 minutes before turning out onto a rack to cool completely.7) Cut cake in half horizontally. Warm 45ml (3 tbsp) jam. Spread over one half, sandwich together and dust with sieved icing sugar. Serves 8-10 3. CURRIED EGGS 1) Fry 1 large chopped onion in 30ml (2 tbsp) oil till soft. Stir in 15ml (1 tbsp) curry paste and fry till fragrant.2) Add 15ml (1 tbsp) fruit chutney and 1 x 400g can chopped tomatoes. Add 1 peeled and chopped Granny Smith apple and simmer for 15 minutes, adding a little stock if too thick.3) Add a handful of frozen peas and 6 peeled hard-boiled eggs. Heat through for 5-8 minutes. Serve with rice and sambals. Serves 6